2023-05-31 06:32 PM;,"In August 2021, India's Defense Ministry announced that it would abolish all existing cantonments and military stations in the country and replace them with ""new cantonments"" in a bid to optimize land use and make better use of precious resources. The announcement has stirred debate in neighboring Pakistan, where cantonments have long been an integral part of the country's military and political landscape.
